oai_dc:dc.dc:title: PHOTOLYTIC STUDIES OF 1-(3'-QUINOLYL)PROPYNAL TOSYLHYDRAZONE SODIUM-SALT
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: SEKHER, P
SACHDEVA, R
TALWAR, SS
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Detailed photodecomposition of 1-(3'-quinolyl)propynal tosylhydrazone sodium salt in methanol and acetonitrile-two polar solvents is described. Time evolution of photolytic absorption spectra and GC-MS study of the photolytic products have been carried out to identify the intermediate diazo compound, and the environmental effects on the product distribution from the carbene generated.
oai_dc:dc.dc:identifier: INDIAN JOURNAL OF CHEMISTRY SECTION B-ORGANIC CHEMISTRY INCLUDING MEDICINAL CHEMISTRY, 34(7), 581-586
